Description: Pottery: jar; red-brown Nile clay with abundant fine mica and occasional medium-coarse lime and grits; ovoid bag-shaped body with pointed base; neck and rim missing.
Curator's comments: Parallels from Kom Firin. See also Ptolemaic ink well from Naukratis (Bailey 2008, no. 3673).
Cf. Wilson, K. (1982), Cities of the Delta II. Mendes, pl. xv, 5.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IB.046)
